--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 70c970a7d9f7d414994564bd048e8a6d, type: 3}
  m_Name: UFO_Credible_Generic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: KBTV.Runtime::KBTV.Dialogue.CallerDialogueTemplate
  Topic: {fileID: 0}
  Legitimacy: 2
  Priority: 1
  Length: 10
  IntroLines:
  - Text: Vern, I've been listening for years and I finally have my own sighting
      to report.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I never thought I'd be making this call, but here I am.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: So I was out stargazing Tuesday night when something appeared that wasn't
      on any chart.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  DetailLines:
  - Text: Three amber lights in a triangle formation, completely silent, hovering
      for about two minutes before shooting off.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: It moved against the wind, no sound, no blinking lights like a plane would
      have.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I timed it - ninety seconds of hovering, then acceleration that would flatten
      any pilot.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  DefenseLines:
  - Text: I've worked at the airport for fifteen years. I know aircraft. This wasn't
      one.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'm an amateur astronomer. I know what satellites look like. This was different.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My whole family saw it. We're not all crazy, Vern.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  AcceptanceLines:
  - Text: I knew you'd understand. Nobody else believes me.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Thank god. My wife thinks I've lost it.
    Tone: 10
    Weight: 1
  - Text: That's exactly what I was hoping to hear.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDetailLines:
  - Text: I managed to get a few photos. They're not great, but you can clearly see
      the triangle formation.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The way it moved... it was like physics didn't apply. No aircraft I know
      of can do that.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I've checked flight trackers, satellite databases. Nothing was supposed
      to be there.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDefenseLines: []
  ConclusionLines:
  - Text: Thanks Vern. I'll send you the photos if I can get them developed.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Keep doing what you're doing. People need to hear this stuff.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I'll keep watching and call back if it happens again.
    Tone: 1
    Weight: 1
